   299→     * @return {@link FetchRequest.Builder} that can be submitted to the broker
   300→     */
   301→    protected FetchRequest.Builder createFetchRequest(final Node fetchTarget,
   302→                                                      final FetchSessionHandler.FetchRequestData requestData) {
   303→        // Version 12 is the maximum version that could be used without topic IDs. See FetchRequest.json for schema
   304→        // changelog.
   305→        final short maxVersion = requestData.canUseTopicIds() ? ApiKeys.FETCH.latestVersion() : (short) 12;
   306→
   307→        final FetchRequest.Builder request = FetchRequest.Builder
   308→                .forConsumer(maxVersion, fetchConfig.maxWaitMs, fetchConfig.minBytes, requestData.toSend())
   309→                .isolationLevel(fetchConfig.isolationLevel)
   310→                .setMaxBytes(fetchConfig.maxBytes)
   311→                .metadata(requestData.metadata())
   312→                .removed(requestData.toForget())
   313→                .replaced(requestData.toReplace())
   314→                .rackId(fetchConfig.clientRackId);
   315→
   316→        log.debug("Sending {} {} to broker {}", fetchConfig.isolationLevel, requestData, fetchTarget);
   317→
   318→        // We add the node to the set of nodes with pending fetch requests before adding the
   319→        // listener because the future may have been fulfilled on another thread (e.g. during a
   320→        // disconnection being handled by the heartbeat thread) which will mean the listener
   321→        // will be invoked synchronously.
   322→        log.debug("Adding pending request for node {}", fetchTarget);
   323→        nodesWithPendingFetchRequests.add(fetchTarget.id());
   324→
   325→        return request;
   326→    }
   327→
   328→    /**
   329→     * Return the set of <em>fetchable</em> partitions, which are the set of partitions to which we are subscribed,
   330→     * but <em>excluding</em> any partitions for which we still have buffered data. The idea is that since the user
   331→     * has yet to process the data for the partition that has already been fetched, we should not go send for more data
   332→     * until the previously-fetched data has been processed.
   333→     *
   334→     * @param buffered The set of partitions we have in our buffer
   335→     * @return {@link Set} of {@link TopicPartition topic partitions} for which we should fetch data
   336→     */
   337→    private Set<TopicPartition> fetchablePartitions(Set<TopicPartition> buffered) {
   338→        // This is the test that returns true if the partition is *not* buffered
   339→        Predicate<TopicPartition> isNotBuffered = tp -> !buffered.contains(tp);
   340→
   341→        // Return all partitions that are in an otherwise fetchable state *and* for which we don't already have some
   342→        // messages sitting in our buffer.
   343→        return new HashSet<>(subscriptions.fetchablePartitions(isNotBuffered));
   344→    }
   345→
   346→    /**
   347→     * Determine from which replica to read: the <i>preferred</i> or the <i>leader</i>. The preferred replica is used
   348→     * iff:
   349→     *
   350→     * <ul>
   351→     *     <li>A preferred replica was previously set</li>
   352→     *     <li>We're still within the lease time for the preferred replica</li>
   353→     *     <li>The replica is still online/available</li>
